Dialogue: 0,00:00:00.000,00:00:00.900,辉英,,0,0,0,,We're trying to decide.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:01.600,00:00:03.780,辉英,,0,0,0,,We have a couple of integral equation problems,
Dialogue: 0,00:00:03.940,00:00:07.740,辉英,,0,0,0,,short ones that we're going to talk about in evening settings,
Dialogue: 0,00:00:07.880,00:00:08.840,辉英,,0,0,0,,which we'll do next week.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:09.580,00:00:12.060,辉英,,0,0,0,,And then there's also, I guess, some discussion
Dialogue: 0,00:00:12.060,00:00:13.040,辉英,,0,0,0,,about the final project.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:13.280,00:00:15.600,辉英,,0,0,0,,I don't know if you all have opinions about this.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:15.780,00:00:18.260,辉英,,0,0,0,,You should express them to Professor Lang.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:19.280,00:00:20.880,辉英,,0,0,0,,We will take them under advisement.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:21.880,00:00:22.840,辉英,,0,0,0,,But we'll try to.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:22.960,00:00:25.080,辉英,,0,0,0,,I work very mindful of not packing a lot of work
Dialogue: 0,00:00:25.080,00:00:26.060,辉英,,0,0,0,,in the last week of classes.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:26.060,00:00:31.840,辉英,,0,0,0,,So for today, I'm going to talk about quadrature
Dialogue: 0,00:00:31.840,00:00:37.240,辉英,,0,0,0,,and the video from yesterday's Monday's lecture.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:37.640,00:00:38.640,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's getting there.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:38.880,00:00:41.460,辉英,,0,0,0,,I have to compress it, I guess, before I can post it.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:42.080,00:00:44.500,辉英,,0,0,0,,But it should be up by tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:44.640,00:00:47.120,辉英,,0,0,0,,I just have a little video for this one, too.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:47.540,00:00:48.880,辉英,,0,0,0,,The camera is running at the moment.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:50.360,00:00:52.540,辉英,,0,0,0,,I haven't officially asked for any of you
Dialogue: 0,00:00:52.540,00:00:53.860,辉英,,0,0,0,,for signed disclosures.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:53.860,00:00:55.600,辉英,,0,0,0,,I don't think anybody showed up.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:55.600,00:00:56.040,辉英,,0,0,0,,Do you show up?
Dialogue: 0,00:00:56.060,00:00:56.580,辉英,,0,0,0,,I don't think anybody showed up on the video.
Dialogue: 0,00:00:56.760,00:00:59.360,辉英,,0,0,0,,Your voice might play on the video.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:00.120,00:01:01.520,辉英,,0,0,0,,If you have objections to this,
Dialogue: 0,00:01:01.800,00:01:05.520,辉英,,0,0,0,,certainly feel free to mention them to me
Dialogue: 0,00:01:05.520,00:01:07.120,辉英,,0,0,0,,and we'll figure out something.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:09.020,00:01:12.220,辉英,,0,0,0,,Okay, so we're going to talk about numerical quadrature.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:12.960,00:01:15.360,辉英,,0,0,0,,And many of you may have seen Gauss.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:15.420,00:01:16.960,辉英,,0,0,0,,How many of you have used Gauss quadrature?
Dialogue: 0,00:01:17.800,00:01:19.800,辉英,,0,0,0,,How many of you have seen an analysis
Dialogue: 0,00:01:19.800,00:01:22.080,辉英,,0,0,0,,of how the formulas are derived?
Dialogue: 0,00:01:23.840,00:01:24.620,辉英,,0,0,0,,A couple.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:24.620,00:01:25.620,辉英,,0,0,0,,Okay, so for those of you...
Dialogue: 0,00:01:26.060,00:01:27.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,For those of you who have seen this before,
Dialogue: 0,00:01:27.760,00:01:28.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,this won't be new.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:28.760,00:01:30.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And for those who haven't seen it before,
Dialogue: 0,00:01:30.760,00:01:31.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,I guess it won't be,
Dialogue: 0,00:01:31.760,00:01:34.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is not exactly a very informative statement,
Dialogue: 0,00:01:34.760,00:01:35.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,but there it is.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:35.760,00:01:36.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So we're going to...
Dialogue: 0,00:01:36.760,00:01:38.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,I'm going to go through a little bit of it.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:38.760,00:01:40.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And the reason we're going to talk about quadrature
Dialogue: 0,00:01:40.760,00:01:42.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and the ways in which you derive quadrature formulas
Dialogue: 0,00:01:42.760,00:01:44.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,is it will really lead into the next lecture,
Dialogue: 0,00:01:44.760,00:01:46.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is how you take these ideas from quadrature,
Dialogue: 0,00:01:46.760,00:01:48.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,which you may or may not have seen before,
Dialogue: 0,00:01:48.760,00:01:50.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and how you can use them to develop
Dialogue: 0,00:01:50.760,00:01:51.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,the next lecture.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:51.760,00:01:53.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So I'm going to go through a little bit of it.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:53.760,00:01:54.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I'm going to talk about the idea of quadrature,
Dialogue: 0,00:01:54.760,00:01:55.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,which you may or may not have seen before.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:55.760,00:01:57.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So you can use them to actually come up with methods
Dialogue: 0,00:01:57.760,00:01:59.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,for solving integral equations.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:59.760,00:02:02.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And give you a method that's really extraordinarily effective
Dialogue: 0,00:02:02.760,00:02:04.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,in two space dimensions.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:04.760,00:02:06.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And doesn't necessarily generalize that easily
Dialogue: 0,00:02:06.760,00:02:08.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,to three dimensions,
Dialogue: 0,00:02:08.760,00:02:11.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,although there have been some recent improvements in that.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:11.760,00:02:14.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So part of the reason we're talking about quadrature
Dialogue: 0,00:02:14.760,00:02:17.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,is to fill in some background in case you're missing it,
Dialogue: 0,00:02:17.760,00:02:21.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,but partly because it's going to lead us right into
Dialogue: 0,00:02:21.760,00:02:23.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,a very effective way,
Dialogue: 0,00:02:23.760,00:02:25.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,one of the most effective ways of solving it,
Dialogue: 0,00:02:25.760,00:02:27.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,is to use the idea of integral equations
Dialogue: 0,00:02:27.760,00:02:29.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,in two space dimensions.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:29.760,00:02:31.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,All right, so what do we mean by quadrature?
Dialogue: 0,00:02:31.760,00:02:34.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And that is we're going to approximate an integral
Dialogue: 0,00:02:34.760,00:02:37.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,by, which is of course just the area under a curve,
Dialogue: 0,00:02:37.760,00:02:40.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and we want to do it with some formula.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:40.760,00:02:44.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,That is we're going to use values of a function and weights.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:44.760,00:02:46.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So if you're doing an integral from zero to one,
Dialogue: 0,00:02:46.760,00:02:48.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,which we'll probably do,
Dialogue: 0,00:02:48.760,00:02:50.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,we don't have the integral in that because
Dialogue: 0,00:02:50.760,00:02:53.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,I'm just going to integrate this out to the x,
Dialogue: 0,00:02:53.760,00:02:55.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I'm trying to get the area under the curve.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:55.760,00:02:57.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,I'm doing one.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:57.760,00:03:04.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I'm going to approximate it with this box card
Dialogue: 0,00:03:04.760,00:03:10.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,of height f and I'm evaluating it at x.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:10.760,00:03:14.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So that's not a very difficult quadrature scheme.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:14.760,00:03:21.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's an approximation,
Dialogue: 0,00:03:21.760,00:03:23.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and we can come up with better approximations,
Dialogue: 0,00:03:23.760,00:03:25.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and the obvious one is, well,
Dialogue: 0,00:03:25.760,00:03:28.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,if it doesn't work to approximate your function
Dialogue: 0,00:03:28.760,00:03:31.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,with one box card, maybe two will,
Dialogue: 0,00:03:31.760,00:03:33.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,box cards would be better.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:33.760,00:03:37.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So I'm sure all of you have learned this in calculus
Dialogue: 0,00:03:37.760,00:03:42.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,that it would be better to use more box cards
Dialogue: 0,00:03:42.760,00:03:44.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,when you do the Rubin sum.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:44.760,00:03:46.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,But before we do that, let's talk a little bit about
Dialogue: 0,00:03:46.760,00:03:49.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,just this box card and what it's accurate for.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:49.760,00:03:54.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So the extraordinary thing about that one box card
Dialogue: 0,00:03:54.760,00:03:58.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,is of course it's exact for a function that's a constant
Dialogue: 0,00:03:58.760,00:04:01.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,on the integral 0 to 1.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:01.760,00:04:07.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's also exact for anything that's a constant or a linear.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:07.760,00:04:11.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So it's actually a single point quadrature scheme.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:11.760,00:04:14.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's a lot more powerful than you think it is,
Dialogue: 0,00:04:14.760,00:04:20.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and in fact it's more powerful than if I use one point on the x.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:20.760,00:04:23.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So suppose I look at these functions that are linear,
Dialogue: 0,00:04:23.760,00:04:25.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I want to get the area of the curve,
Dialogue: 0,00:04:25.760,00:04:32.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I have three choices about how to approximate it.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:32.760,00:04:44.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,I could use a point at the beginning of the integral,
Dialogue: 0,00:04:44.760,00:04:47.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,so I could use f of 0,
Dialogue: 0,00:04:47.760,00:04:52.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,or I could use, for that same linear function,
Dialogue: 0,00:04:52.760,00:05:03.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,f of 1.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:03.760,00:05:09.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And what can I say immediately about both these methods?
Dialogue: 0,00:05:09.760,00:05:15.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Do they work if the function is constant?
Dialogue: 0,00:05:15.760,00:05:19.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,If f of x equals a constant,
Dialogue: 0,00:05:19.760,00:05:22.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,are these formulas exact?
Dialogue: 0,00:05:22.760,00:05:23.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,All three.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:23.760,00:05:28.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So we can sometimes call this one the midpoint,
Dialogue: 0,00:05:28.760,00:05:33.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and both of these are called endpoint methods.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:35.760,00:05:39.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,The endpoint methods are exact.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:43.760,00:05:50.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,If it's constant, what if f of x is equal to a x plus a p?
Dialogue: 0,00:05:52.760,00:05:58.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Which of these formulas are exact?
Dialogue: 0,00:05:58.760,00:06:00.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,The midpoint and the endpoint?
Dialogue: 0,00:06:00.760,00:06:02.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Midpoint only.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:09.760,00:06:12.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So we could sometimes, if we want to be formal about it,
Dialogue: 0,00:06:12.760,00:06:17.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,we could say the endpoint methods are good for polynomials of order 0,
Dialogue: 0,00:06:17.760,00:06:21.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and the midpoint methods are good for polynomials of order 0 and order 1.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:22.760,00:06:26.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,That, in fact, that idea, the simple idea,
Dialogue: 0,00:06:26.760,00:06:29.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,thinking about what kind of polynomials, functions,
Dialogue: 0,00:06:29.760,00:06:32.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,you could exactly integrate the error out of the curve of,
Dialogue: 0,00:06:32.760,00:06:35.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,is the heart of everything you're going to learn about quadrature.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:35.760,00:06:41.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So everything else I'm going to tell you is an extension of that idea.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:41.760,00:06:43.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,We look at quadrature formulas,
Dialogue: 0,00:06:43.760,00:06:46.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and we're going to ask questions about how high an order of polynomial
Dialogue: 0,00:06:46.760,00:06:48.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,we can exactly integrate.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:48.760,00:06:51.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And that's going to tell us some way of comparing these methods.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:51.760,00:06:54.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So in this very simple setting,
Dialogue: 0,00:06:54.760,00:06:58.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,we're going to start talking about a lot of things about these polynomials.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:58.760,00:07:01.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,But just keep in mind that simple idea.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:01.760,00:07:04.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,We're going to try to come up with methods
Dialogue: 0,00:07:04.760,00:07:08.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,that can accurately integrate higher and higher order polynomials,
Dialogue: 0,00:07:08.760,00:07:12.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and that's how we're going to assess which method is better and which method is worse.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:12.760,00:07:20.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, if we want a method that's more accurate than the midpoint method,
Dialogue: 0,00:07:20.760,00:07:26.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,if our function is not a constant or a linear function,
Dialogue: 0,00:07:26.760,00:07:29.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,it's not a zero-th or first-order polynomial,
Dialogue: 0,00:07:29.760,00:07:33.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,then we could break it up into two box cards.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:33.760,00:07:37.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Does that accurately integrate a higher-order polynomial?
Dialogue: 0,00:07:37.760,00:07:41.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,That is, if I use two box cards in the midpoint method,
Dialogue: 0,00:07:41.760,00:07:44.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,can I exactly integrate any quadratic?
Dialogue: 0,00:07:50.760,00:07:55.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,What about if I use, instead of the midpoints for these two box cards,
Dialogue: 0,00:07:55.760,00:07:57.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,what if I used endpoints?
Dialogue: 0,00:07:57.760,00:08:01.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Would that exactly integrate any quadratic?
Dialogue: 0,00:08:01.760,00:08:04.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, what about a linear function?
Dialogue: 0,00:08:04.760,00:08:08.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,If I use two box cards, will the midpoint method exactly integrate
Dialogue: 0,00:08:08.760,00:08:11.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,a zero-th or first-order polynomial?
Dialogue: 0,00:08:11.760,00:08:15.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,If it's a straight line and I write this up into two box cards,
Dialogue: 0,00:08:15.760,00:08:19.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,will the midpoint method still integrate the linear case?
Dialogue: 0,00:08:19.760,00:08:20.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:20.760,00:08:22.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,What about if I use the endpoint method?
Dialogue: 0,00:08:22.760,00:08:25.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Will it integrate a linear one exactly?
Dialogue: 0,00:08:25.760,00:08:26.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:26.760,00:08:31.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, breaking up into more box cards, more sections,
Dialogue: 0,00:08:31.760,00:08:34.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,doesn't necessarily get you a higher-order polynomial
Dialogue: 0,00:08:34.760,00:08:37.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,unless you try to arrange for it.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:37.760,00:08:39.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, that's another thing you're going to worry about,
Dialogue: 0,00:08:39.760,00:08:42.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is, what should we do if we use lots of points?
Dialogue: 0,00:08:42.760,00:08:47.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And just using equal weights on the two points may not be the best thing to do,
Dialogue: 0,00:08:47.760,00:08:49.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,although, surprisingly,
Dialogue: 0,00:08:49.760,00:08:52.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,in important cases, it is, in fact, the best thing to do.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:52.760,00:08:53.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:53.760,00:08:56.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, but this is going to be our general problem.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:56.760,00:08:59.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,We're going to imagine, well, we can evaluate the function.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:59.760,00:09:01.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Presumably, you can evaluate the function.
Dialogue: 0,00:09:01.760,00:09:03.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,You don't want to evaluate the function too much
Dialogue: 0,00:09:03.760,00:09:06.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,because the function may be expensive to evaluate.
Dialogue: 0,00:09:06.760,00:09:10.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,It might be the result of some complicated calculation you're doing.
Dialogue: 0,00:09:10.760,00:09:15.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,It may be something as simple as evaluating 1 over r, 1 over distance.
Dialogue: 0,00:09:15.760,00:09:19.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,But usually, you want to minimize the number of evaluations you have to do.
Dialogue: 0,00:09:19.760,00:09:21.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And get the best answer you can get.
Dialogue: 0,00:09:21.760,00:09:23.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And you have two degrees of freedom.
Dialogue: 0,00:09:23.760,00:09:27.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I want to keep in mind these two degrees of freedom.
Dialogue: 0,00:09:27.760,00:09:37.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, we have, well, I should say, two types of degrees of freedom.
Dialogue: 0,00:09:46.760,00:09:48.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,The first type is
Dialogue: 0,00:09:48.760,00:09:51.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,the weights for each point.
Dialogue: 0,00:09:54.760,00:09:57.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,For each of the box charts, how much do you weight that point?
Dialogue: 0,00:09:57.760,00:10:00.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And the second type is where to put the points.
Dialogue: 0,00:10:07.760,00:10:11.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And in looking at the midpoints of these two endpoint methods,
Dialogue: 0,00:10:11.760,00:10:12.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,we pick the weight of 1.
Dialogue: 0,00:10:12.760,00:10:14.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,We only have one point.
Dialogue: 0,00:10:14.760,00:10:17.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, weights, the freedom to pick weights doesn't really come into it.
Dialogue: 0,00:10:18.760,00:10:21.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,But we can see already, even in a one point quadrature scheme,
Dialogue: 0,00:10:21.760,00:10:24.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,that degree of freedom of where to put the weights,
Dialogue: 0,00:10:24.760,00:10:27.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,where to put them, that's an important degree of freedom.
Dialogue: 0,00:10:27.760,00:10:30.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And if we use something like a midpoint rule
Dialogue: 0,00:10:30.760,00:10:33.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,for each one of a set, a collection of n boxes,
Dialogue: 0,00:10:33.760,00:10:37.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,we would put 1 over n as the weights, all weights being the same.
Dialogue: 0,00:10:37.760,00:10:41.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And each of the test points would be in the center of each of those box charts.
Dialogue: 0,00:10:41.760,00:10:45.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, that's a general midpoint formula.
Dialogue: 0,00:10:45.760,00:10:47.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And you might ask the question, is that the best thing to do?
Dialogue: 0,00:10:47.760,00:10:50.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Could you put the points in different locations?
Dialogue: 0,00:10:50.760,00:10:53.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Could you use different weights?
Dialogue: 0,00:10:53.760,00:10:59.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, if I have an endpoint scheme, how many degrees of freedom do I have?
Dialogue: 0,00:11:03.760,00:11:06.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, I've got n box charts.
Dialogue: 0,00:11:06.760,00:11:10.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,I can pick n points to, n places to put the,
Dialogue: 0,00:11:10.760,00:11:14.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,I can make the box charts thicker, thinner, so I can put the points anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,00:11:14.760,00:11:16.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,I've got n points to place.
Dialogue: 0,00:11:16.760,00:11:18.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,What about the weights?
Dialogue: 0,00:11:18.760,00:11:20.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Do I have n degrees of freedom in the weights?
Dialogue: 0,00:11:22.760,00:11:24.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,How many degrees of freedom do I have?
Dialogue: 0,00:11:24.760,00:11:26.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,What do I know about the weights?
Dialogue: 0,00:11:26.760,00:11:28.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,They all have to sum to 1.
Dialogue: 0,00:11:28.760,00:11:30.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Why do they have to sum to 1?
Dialogue: 0,00:11:32.760,00:11:35.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Suppose f of x were a constant of 1.
Dialogue: 0,00:11:36.760,00:11:40.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Then that formula should produce exactly the right integral,
Dialogue: 0,00:11:40.760,00:11:42.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,which would be 1.
Dialogue: 0,00:11:42.760,00:11:44.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, that's why the weights have to sum to 1.
Dialogue: 0,00:11:44.760,00:11:46.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,But that idea doesn't exist.
Dialogue: 0,00:11:46.760,00:11:48.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,The idea that the weights have to sum to 1,
Dialogue: 0,00:11:48.760,00:11:52.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,when you think about that, yeah, of course,
Dialogue: 0,00:11:52.760,00:11:55.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,because it's got to integrate the constant function exactly,
Dialogue: 0,00:11:55.760,00:12:01.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,but that's like saying the weights have to be such that the 0th order polynomial gets integrated exactly.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:03.760,00:12:05.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,We get another condition on the weights,
Dialogue: 0,00:12:05.760,00:12:10.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,so that we exactly integrate a constant and a first order polynomial.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:10.760,00:12:16.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, we're going to think a little bit about that.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:16.760,00:12:24.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, there are three different methods we could look at.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:24.760,00:12:28.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,We could use one method, which is an endpoint method.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:28.760,00:12:31.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,We use the beginning of each of these box bars.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:31.760,00:12:33.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,A second method, the one we've been looking at mostly,
Dialogue: 0,00:12:33.760,00:12:34.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,is a midpoint method.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:34.760,00:12:36.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,We pick up points in the middle.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:36.760,00:12:39.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And the third one is sometimes referred to as the trapezoidal rule.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:39.760,00:12:42.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And why is it called the trapezoidal rule?
Dialogue: 0,00:12:42.760,00:12:51.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because you can't see it here, because it's not clear enough in the picture.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:51.760,00:12:54.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,But each of these things are trapezoids.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:54.760,00:12:58.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,They're straight line approximations for whatever that function is.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:58.760,00:13:01.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Which is the best one to use?
Dialogue: 0,00:13:01.760,00:13:08.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Is the trapezoidal one better, or the midpoint one?
Dialogue: 0,00:13:08.760,00:13:10.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Midpoint.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:10.760,00:13:11.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Say again?
Dialogue: 0,00:13:11.760,00:13:12.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Midpoint.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:12.760,00:13:15.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, it turns out the midpoint one is better.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:15.760,00:13:20.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,The trapezoidal rule is, it's putting a straight line between points.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:20.760,00:13:23.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, I'm going to draw a picture of that so you can see why.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:25.760,00:13:27.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, imagine I have a curve like this,
Dialogue: 0,00:13:27.760,00:13:29.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I deal with the trapezoidal rule,
Dialogue: 0,00:13:29.760,00:13:31.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I just exaggerate it.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:31.760,00:13:33.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, these are going to be my trapezoids.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:38.760,00:13:53.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, I've got two trapezoids.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:53.760,00:13:56.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I have an error.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:01.760,00:14:04.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,For that same curve, what would the midpoint rule do?
Dialogue: 0,00:14:08.760,00:14:10.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,I have my two box cards.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:10.760,00:14:12.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,What does the midpoint rule do?
Dialogue: 0,00:14:15.760,00:14:17.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's going to use the point square.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:26.760,00:14:29.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,If I use the midpoint rule, what value am I going to use?
Dialogue: 0,00:14:29.760,00:14:30.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,A middle.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:30.760,00:14:32.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I'm going to pick a middle point.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:35.760,00:14:36.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And that means,
Dialogue: 0,00:14:36.760,00:14:38.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,my midpoint rule looks like this.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:43.760,00:14:44.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, by looking at these two pictures,
Dialogue: 0,00:14:44.760,00:14:47.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,it should be obvious to you that the midpoint rule is going to be better.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:47.760,00:14:48.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,00:14:48.760,00:14:50.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Is that obvious?
Dialogue: 0,00:14:51.760,00:14:53.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Is the terror smaller?
Dialogue: 0,00:14:57.760,00:14:59.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,If I drew a slightly different curve,
Dialogue: 0,00:14:59.760,00:15:01.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,could I get a different answer to this question?
Dialogue: 0,00:15:04.760,00:15:05.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Maybe.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:06.760,00:15:09.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,If I happen to pick a piecewise constant curve,
Dialogue: 0,00:15:09.760,00:15:11.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,my curve is this, the rooftop,
Dialogue: 0,00:15:11.760,00:15:16.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,then trapezoidal and midpoint will both get exactly the right answer.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:17.760,00:15:18.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,After that?
Dialogue: 0,00:15:19.760,00:15:20.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Alright, so,
Dialogue: 0,00:15:21.760,00:15:24.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,it can be a little difficult to decide some of these questions,
Dialogue: 0,00:15:24.760,00:15:27.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,even in this simple setting, about error.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:27.760,00:15:30.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And so, we need some more formal methods to think about it.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:30.760,00:15:33.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And it also turns out we need some tricks.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:33.760,00:15:35.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Well, numerical insights.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:36.760,00:15:40.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,It will help us actually come up with ideas about where to put points
Dialogue: 0,00:15:40.760,00:15:42.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and how to set weights.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:42.760,00:15:43.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Alright, so,
Dialogue: 0,00:15:43.760,00:15:46.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,for the moment, we're going to worry about
Dialogue: 0,00:15:46.760,00:15:48.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,a general, positive formula,
Dialogue: 0,00:15:48.760,00:15:52.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,where we think of picking the weights
Dialogue: 0,00:15:52.760,00:15:54.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and picking the evaluation points,
Dialogue: 0,00:15:54.760,00:15:57.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and that will give us 2n degrees of freedom.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:57.760,00:15:59.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Where the way you normally think of the weights,
Dialogue: 0,00:15:59.760,00:16:01.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,I can double the weights up to sum to 1,
Dialogue: 0,00:16:01.760,00:16:03.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,that's a constraint.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:03.760,00:16:05.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And we're going to see if we want,
Dialogue: 0,00:16:05.760,00:16:09.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,that's a constraint to make sure that we get the exact answer for a constant.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:09.760,00:16:12.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,But it's one of a whole family of constraints.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:12.760,00:16:15.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, we're going to think about having these 2n degrees of freedom,
Dialogue: 0,00:16:15.760,00:16:19.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,but we're going to very quickly see that we're going to need to put some constraints on it
Dialogue: 0,00:16:19.760,00:16:21.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,to try to get good accuracy.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:21.760,00:16:23.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, we're going to pick the evaluation points,
Dialogue: 0,00:16:23.760,00:16:25.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and we're going to pick the weights.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:25.760,00:16:27.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, how should we do that?
Dialogue: 0,00:16:28.760,00:16:31.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, we already started talking about the key idea.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:31.760,00:16:33.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,What I said was the key idea.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:33.760,00:16:34.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,The polynomial.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:35.760,00:16:37.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,We are going to say I have this function,
Dialogue: 0,00:16:37.760,00:16:43.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I'm going to say I can approximate it well with a polynomial up to Lth order.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:43.760,00:16:47.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And what we're going to try to do is to pick the points and the weights,
Dialogue: 0,00:16:47.760,00:16:52.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,so that it accurately integrates any polynomial up to as high an order as possible.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:55.760,00:17:02.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, we can, by picking the points and the weights,
Dialogue: 0,00:17:02.760,00:17:04.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,because we have 2n degrees of freedom,
Dialogue: 0,00:17:05.760,00:17:08.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,we can actually come up with points and weights
Dialogue: 0,00:17:08.760,00:17:14.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,that will exactly integrate any polynomial up to the Lth order,
Dialogue: 0,00:17:14.760,00:17:17.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,where the Lth order is 2n minus 1.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:18.760,00:17:20.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Why 2n minus 1?
Dialogue: 0,00:17:20.760,00:17:22.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,What does the minus 1 tell you?
Dialogue: 0,00:17:24.760,00:17:29.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, how many coefficients does an Lth order polynomial have if I write it this way?
Dialogue: 0,00:17:32.760,00:17:34.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Well, because I wrote it from a0 and a1,
Dialogue: 0,00:17:35.760,00:17:37.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,all the way to aL.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:37.760,00:17:40.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,If you're a programmer and you write software a lot,
Dialogue: 0,00:17:40.760,00:17:45.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,you count from 0, then of course you know that's L plus 1 coefficients.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:45.760,00:17:47.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,That's where the 1 is coming from.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:47.760,00:17:51.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,The Lth is the order, but the number of degrees of freedom is L plus 1.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:51.760,00:17:57.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, we can get to an Lth order polynomial means we have L plus 1 coefficients
Dialogue: 0,00:17:57.760,00:18:02.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,of that polynomial, and that we're going to match to the degrees of freedom
Dialogue: 0,00:18:02.760,00:18:06.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,in our quadrature scheme.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:06.760,00:18:09.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, we have 2n coefficients we have to find,
Dialogue: 0,00:18:09.760,00:18:13.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and that means we can match 2n coefficients of a polynomial,
Dialogue: 0,00:18:13.760,00:18:18.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and that means L plus 1 is equal to 2n, or L equals 2n minus 1.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:18.760,00:18:22.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, that should be easy.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:22.760,00:18:25.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, how are we going to do that?
Dialogue: 0,00:18:25.760,00:18:28.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,I've got points and weights,
Dialogue: 0,00:18:28.760,00:18:31.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I want to make sure that we pick the points and the weights,
Dialogue: 0,00:18:31.760,00:18:37.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,so we exactly integrate any polynomial of order up to L.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:37.760,00:18:44.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,How do I figure out where those points and weights are?
Dialogue: 0,00:18:44.760,00:18:48.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Can I write down a system of equations and solve it?
Dialogue: 0,00:18:48.760,00:18:51.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Can I just go ahead and do that?
Dialogue: 0,00:18:51.760,00:18:54.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,We're going to talk about that in a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:54.760,00:18:57.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,But I wanted to say something about the error estimates,
Dialogue: 0,00:18:57.760,00:19:00.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,because these methods, when you do this,
Dialogue: 0,00:19:00.760,00:19:05.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,doing the midpoint rule with boxcars,
Dialogue: 0,00:19:05.760,00:19:08.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,or doing something like this, where you pick the points and weights
Dialogue: 0,00:19:08.760,00:19:12.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,to exactly integrate as high an order polynomial as possible,
Dialogue: 0,00:19:12.760,00:19:15.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,they have very different convergence properties.
Dialogue: 0,00:19:15.760,00:19:18.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,The Gaussian quadrature, or any quadrature scheme,
Dialogue: 0,00:19:18.760,00:19:21.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,based on trying to match as high an order polynomial as possible,
Dialogue: 0,00:19:21.760,00:19:26.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,has what we call spectral convergence.
Dialogue: 0,00:19:26.760,00:19:29.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, normally, when you refine a discretization,
Dialogue: 0,00:19:29.760,00:19:35.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,you figure, alright, if it's in a cubic order method,
Dialogue: 0,00:19:35.760,00:19:40.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,you might expect that if I half the number of the step size in my discretization,
Dialogue: 0,00:19:40.760,00:19:43.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,then maybe the error goes down by a factor of 8.
Dialogue: 0,00:19:43.760,00:19:46.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Or maybe I have a second order method,
Dialogue: 0,00:19:46.760,00:19:48.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and in this case the error goes down by a factor of 4.
Dialogue: 0,00:19:48.760,00:19:51.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Or a first order method goes down by a factor of 2.
Dialogue: 0,00:19:51.760,00:19:54.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,You have this idea that it is the refinement.
Dialogue: 0,00:19:54.760,00:19:58.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,I take the discretization, I use twice as many points,
Dialogue: 0,00:19:58.760,00:20:01.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,I get twice as much accuracy,
Dialogue: 0,00:20:01.760,00:20:05.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,if it's first order, 4 times as much accuracy if it's second order,
Dialogue: 0,00:20:05.760,00:20:08.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,8 times as much accuracy if it's third order.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:08.760,00:20:12.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,What do you think you get with Gaussian quadrature?
Dialogue: 0,00:20:12.760,00:20:16.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, what that formula means, although it's a little hard to tease out from the factorial way,
Dialogue: 0,00:20:16.760,00:20:19.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,it's usually, it's formally presented.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:19.760,00:20:23.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,It says that for every point I add,
Dialogue: 0,00:20:23.760,00:20:26.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,the accuracy increases by a factor of 2.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:26.760,00:20:33.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, it's not going down like 1 over,
Dialogue: 0,00:20:33.760,00:20:39.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,it's not going down linearly or quadratically or cubically with the number of points,
Dialogue: 0,00:20:39.760,00:20:44.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,it's going down exponentially fast with the number of points.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:44.760,00:20:48.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So imagine how many, if you want to get 16 digits of accuracy,
Dialogue: 0,00:20:48.760,00:20:51.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,2 points gets you 1 digit,
Dialogue: 0,00:20:51.760,00:20:55.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,then 3 points gets you 4 digits.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:55.760,00:20:58.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,4 points gets you 8 digits.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:58.760,00:21:01.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,5 points gets you 16 digits.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:01.760,00:21:03.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,When we're talking about these methods,
Dialogue: 0,00:21:03.760,00:21:08.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,we're talking about methods that have extraordinary rapid convergence
Dialogue: 0,00:21:08.760,00:21:11.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,when they count on certain properties.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:11.760,00:21:14.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And we're going to come back and talk a little bit about what those properties are,
Dialogue: 0,00:21:14.760,00:21:17.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,but unfortunately for the integrals,
Dialogue: 0,00:21:17.760,00:21:20.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,in this class, they violate the properties for which that's true
Dialogue: 0,00:21:20.760,00:21:23.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,in many of the cases, but not all of them.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:23.760,00:21:25.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And we'll look at some important ones that show up in 2D.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:25.760,00:21:28.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Alright, so, let's look at an example.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:28.760,00:21:30.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, it's, you know, I'm going to take,
Dialogue: 0,00:21:30.760,00:21:32.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,alright, what does spectral accuracy mean,
Dialogue: 0,00:21:32.760,00:21:34.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,what does it really look like when we're talking about this?
Dialogue: 0,00:21:34.760,00:21:36.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, I'm taking the sine function,
Dialogue: 0,00:21:36.760,00:21:41.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,I'm going to do the sine function and integrate it with a quadrature scheme
Dialogue: 0,00:21:41.760,00:21:44.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,because we can exactly integrate the sine function with it all.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:44.760,00:21:46.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,I'm going to try to do that in calculus.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:46.760,00:21:47.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And what's true about the sine function?
Dialogue: 0,00:21:47.760,00:21:51.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Why do you think I picked that function?
Dialogue: 0,00:21:51.760,00:21:53.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, do any of its derivatives go to 0?
Dialogue: 0,00:21:53.760,00:21:55.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Is there any polynomial that,
Dialogue: 0,00:21:55.760,00:21:58.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,that exactly describes the sine function?
Dialogue: 0,00:21:58.760,00:22:02.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now, if it did, then I could differentiate the sine function
Dialogue: 0,00:22:02.760,00:22:03.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,a certain number of times,
Dialogue: 0,00:22:03.760,00:22:06.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and at some point the derivatives would go to 0.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:06.760,00:22:07.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,But that never happens, right?
Dialogue: 0,00:22:07.760,00:22:09.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,If I differentiate the sine function,
Dialogue: 0,00:22:09.760,00:22:13.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and differentiate, I get sine, cosine, sine, cosine, sine, cosine, sine, cosine,
Dialogue: 0,00:22:13.760,00:22:15.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,derivative never goes to 0.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:15.760,00:22:19.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, it's not described exactly by a finite number of polynomials.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:19.760,00:22:22.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And it gives us a chance to look at the convergence properties
Dialogue: 0,00:22:22.760,00:22:25.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,of a method for which we actually know the exact number.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:25.760,00:22:27.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, let's look at the answer.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:27.760,00:22:30.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, this is the error analysis,
Dialogue: 0,00:22:30.760,00:22:32.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and this is looking at the point,
Dialogue: 0,00:22:32.760,00:22:36.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,the log-log plot of error versus number of points.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:36.760,00:22:40.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And if you look at this scheme and say,
Dialogue: 0,00:22:40.760,00:22:42.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,well, what happens when I increase the number of points
Dialogue: 0,00:22:42.760,00:22:44.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,by an order of magnitude?
Dialogue: 0,00:22:44.760,00:22:47.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,What happens to the error in this plot?
Dialogue: 0,00:22:47.760,00:22:51.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, an order of magnitude increases the number of quadrature points,
Dialogue: 0,00:22:51.760,00:22:54.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,meaning I break it up into an order of magnitude and one section,
Dialogue: 0,00:22:54.760,00:22:57.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and an order of magnitude, more evaluations.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:57.760,00:23:03.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,How much does the error go down?
Dialogue: 0,00:23:03.760,00:23:04.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Well, you look at it,
Dialogue: 0,00:23:04.760,00:23:07.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,an order of magnitude on the bottom curve looks roughly like,
Dialogue: 0,00:23:07.760,00:23:10.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,how many orders of magnitude on the side?
Dialogue: 0,00:23:10.760,00:23:13.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, we're looking at a plot of error versus number of points.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:13.760,00:23:14.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Two looks sort of like,
Dialogue: 0,00:23:14.760,00:23:16.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and that would be a second-order method.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:16.760,00:23:19.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,You increase the number of points by a factor of 10,
Dialogue: 0,00:23:19.760,00:23:22.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and the error goes down by a factor of 100.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:22.760,00:23:24.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,That seems pretty good.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:24.760,00:23:27.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,It means that, you know, with 1,000 points,
Dialogue: 0,00:23:27.760,00:23:31.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,10,000 points, we can almost get machine precision.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:31.760,00:23:35.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, that's not a quadrature scheme.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:35.760,00:23:39.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,That was, which of these three methods do you think was the midpoint rule
Dialogue: 0,00:23:39.760,00:23:41.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,or the endpoint rule?
Dialogue: 0,00:23:41.760,00:23:43.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it turned out it was the midpoint,
Dialogue: 0,00:23:43.760,00:23:47.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,because the endpoint rule doesn't have such rapid convergence.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:47.760,00:23:49.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now, I'll come back if there's time
Dialogue: 0,00:23:49.760,00:23:51.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and talk a little bit about the Taylor series of values,
Dialogue: 0,00:23:51.760,00:23:53.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,but I just wanted to make a point about it,
Dialogue: 0,00:23:53.760,00:23:57.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,because it's the heart of why the methods that we're using work.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:57.760,00:24:00.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,If I do a Taylor series expansion of a function,
Dialogue: 0,00:24:00.760,00:24:04.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,as long as it has, it's infinitely continuously differentiable.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:04.760,00:24:08.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, sine functions are infinitely continuously differentiable.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:08.760,00:24:10.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Then I can write down the Taylor series expansion
Dialogue: 0,00:24:10.760,00:24:13.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,for f of x at every point x.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:13.760,00:24:17.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And that means up to a Taylor series residual,
Dialogue: 0,00:24:17.760,00:24:21.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,I can write down a polynomial representation of f of x.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:21.760,00:24:23.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And when I do a,
Dialogue: 0,00:24:23.760,00:24:26.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,a quadrature scheme that's exact for that polynomial,
Dialogue: 0,00:24:26.760,00:24:29.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,it means we'll pick up that order for Taylor series,
Dialogue: 0,00:24:29.760,00:24:32.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,but we'll miss out on the remainder term.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:32.760,00:24:35.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And the remainder term for the Taylor series expansion
Dialogue: 0,00:24:35.760,00:24:37.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,is this thing that has a coefficient in front of it
Dialogue: 0,00:24:37.760,00:24:39.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,that goes like the factorial,
Dialogue: 0,00:24:39.760,00:24:41.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and also is the derivative.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:41.760,00:24:44.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, looking at this Taylor series expansion, it says,
Dialogue: 0,00:24:44.760,00:24:48.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,if we're going to do something that's exact for polynomials,
Dialogue: 0,00:24:48.760,00:24:50.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,for progressively higher-order polynomials,
Dialogue: 0,00:24:50.760,00:24:52.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,we want something towards the Taylor series
Dialogue: 0,00:24:52.760,00:24:54.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,remainder theorem works.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:54.760,00:24:58.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,It means we want something that's infinitely differentiable,
Dialogue: 0,00:24:58.760,00:25:01.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and one has to be true about the derivatives.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:01.760,00:25:03.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,These derivatives are going off to infinity
Dialogue: 0,00:25:03.760,00:25:06.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,as you differentiate more and more and more.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:06.760,00:25:08.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,That's not so good.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:08.760,00:25:10.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,If they go up, if the derivatives go up faster
Dialogue: 0,00:25:10.760,00:25:12.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,than the factorial goes down,
Dialogue: 0,00:25:12.760,00:25:14.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,then these methods aren't going to be very good.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:14.760,00:25:16.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, we want things that are smooth
Dialogue: 0,00:25:16.760,00:25:18.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and for which the derivatives don't go up.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:18.760,00:25:21.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And if we do that, then we get this incredibly rapid convergence,
Dialogue: 0,00:25:21.760,00:25:23.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and then it's worth looking at.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:23.760,00:25:26.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Well, I still need to do this.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:26.760,00:25:30.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,I'm going to skip ahead and show you the plot,
Dialogue: 0,00:25:30.760,00:25:33.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and then we'll come back and look at the...
Dialogue: 0,00:25:33.760,00:25:36.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Ah, here.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:36.760,00:25:39.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Alright, so what I showed you in the first plot
Dialogue: 0,00:25:39.760,00:25:42.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,was the simple quadrature scheme, the midpoint rule.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:42.760,00:25:44.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,I'll come back and do all the slides in a bit,
Dialogue: 0,00:25:44.760,00:25:47.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and I just wanted to show you the result at the end.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:47.760,00:25:49.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Simple quad.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:49.760,00:25:51.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,To get to machine precision,
Dialogue: 0,00:25:51.760,00:25:54.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,that midpoint rule would take 10,000 points.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:54.760,00:25:56.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,For Gaussian quadrature,
Dialogue: 0,00:25:56.760,00:25:58.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,in about 11 points,
Dialogue: 0,00:25:58.760,00:26:00.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,you can get to machine precision.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:00.760,00:26:03.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, we're not talking about,
Dialogue: 0,00:26:03.760,00:26:06.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,oh, it's two times faster, or it's four times faster.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:06.760,00:26:08.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,If you're looking for accuracy close to machine precision,
Dialogue: 0,00:26:08.760,00:26:10.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,that is high-accuracy calculations,
Dialogue: 0,00:26:10.760,00:26:12.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,you're talking about, instead of having to do
Dialogue: 0,00:26:12.760,00:26:15.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,10,000 points with a midpoint rule,
Dialogue: 0,00:26:15.760,00:26:18.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,you're talking about doing 11 or 12.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:18.760,00:26:20.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And all you have to do is to figure out
Dialogue: 0,00:26:20.760,00:26:23.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,what the good weights and evaluation points are.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:23.760,00:26:25.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And we'll look at those in a little bit,
Dialogue: 0,00:26:25.760,00:26:28.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,but I want to go back and talk about how we get there.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:30.760,00:26:35.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, we have this idea that any smooth function,
Dialogue: 0,00:26:35.760,00:26:37.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,infinitely differentiable function,
Dialogue: 0,00:26:37.760,00:26:39.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,can be described by a polynomial.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:39.760,00:26:41.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And if we can pick up that polynomial,
Dialogue: 0,00:26:41.760,00:26:44.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,then the remainder term is very small,
Dialogue: 0,00:26:44.760,00:26:46.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and the higher the order of the polynomial,
Dialogue: 0,00:26:46.760,00:26:48.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,the smaller this remainder term is,
Dialogue: 0,00:26:48.760,00:26:50.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and it goes down really, really fast.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:50.760,00:26:56.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, how do we do that?
Dialogue: 0,00:26:56.760,00:26:59.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, we're going to produce this exactness condition,
Dialogue: 0,00:26:59.760,00:27:01.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and we're going to do it on this unit-integral-integral,
Dialogue: 0,00:27:01.760,00:27:03.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,just so we have an example here.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:05.760,00:27:10.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,We're going to try to exactly integrate a polynomial,
Dialogue: 0,00:27:10.760,00:27:12.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,an L-thorough polynomial,
Dialogue: 0,00:27:12.760,00:27:15.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and we're going to try to pick the points and weights
Dialogue: 0,00:27:15.760,00:27:18.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,so we exactly integrate that L-thorough polynomial.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:18.760,00:27:22.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And we can use a lot of properties in this integration.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:22.760,00:27:25.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, let's have a look at this.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:25.760,00:27:27.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,I take an L-thorough polynomial,
Dialogue: 0,00:27:27.760,00:27:29.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,I write out what that L-thorough polynomial is,
Dialogue: 0,00:27:29.760,00:27:33.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,it's this integral from 0 to 1 of a0 plus a1x plus a2x squared, etc.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:33.760,00:27:40.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And I can write it down as this sum of quadrature weights and points.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:40.760,00:27:44.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Remember, we're talking about taking this L-thorough polynomial,
Dialogue: 0,00:27:44.760,00:27:46.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,so we have this thing,
Dialogue: 0,00:27:46.760,00:27:49.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,PL of x,
Dialogue: 0,00:27:49.760,00:27:52.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,on this integral from 0 to 1,
Dialogue: 0,00:27:52.760,00:27:55.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and we're trying to figure out where to put points.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:58.760,00:28:03.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,I've got x1 through x sub n.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:06.760,00:28:08.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,These are our points.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:10.760,00:28:14.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And then we've also got, for a point xi,
Dialogue: 0,00:28:14.760,00:28:16.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,a weight i that we're going to multiply by,
Dialogue: 0,00:28:16.760,00:28:18.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,PL of x on it.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:18.760,00:28:21.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And we want to pick out these points and weights.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:21.760,00:28:24.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So when we're looking at the integral from 0 to 1
Dialogue: 0,00:28:24.760,00:28:26.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,of PL of x,
Dialogue: 0,00:28:26.760,00:28:28.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,dx,
Dialogue: 0,00:28:28.760,00:28:32.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,that's exactly equal to this sum from i equals 1 to n
Dialogue: 0,00:28:32.760,00:28:36.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,of wi PL of xi.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:38.760,00:28:42.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So we want this to be exact for all polys
Dialogue: 0,00:28:42.760,00:28:44.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,up to,
Dialogue: 0,00:28:44.760,00:28:46.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,up to,
Dialogue: 0,00:28:46.760,00:28:49.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,L equals 2n minus 1.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:51.760,00:28:53.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,00:28:53.760,00:28:56.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,we now need a strategy for figuring out what those are,
Dialogue: 0,00:28:56.760,00:29:00.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and we can start to make headway with that strategy
Dialogue: 0,00:29:00.760,00:29:02.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,by just writing down
Dialogue: 0,00:29:02.760,00:29:06.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,the polynomial pulled apart into its different, what are called monomens.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:06.760,00:29:08.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So we have the constant monomial,
Dialogue: 0,00:29:08.760,00:29:11.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,the first-order monomial, the second-order monomial,
Dialogue: 0,00:29:11.760,00:29:12.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and then all the way to the L-thorough monomial.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:12.760,00:29:14.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And monomial, the mon of n, is the constant.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:14.760,00:29:16.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So the constant there just means there's only one,
Dialogue: 0,00:29:16.760,00:29:18.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,you know, if we're talking about the,
Dialogue: 0,00:29:18.760,00:29:20.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,an L-thorough monomial,
Dialogue: 0,00:29:20.760,00:29:22.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,we're just talking about x to the L.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:22.760,00:29:24.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,There's no x to the L minus 1,
Dialogue: 0,00:29:24.760,00:29:25.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,x to the L minus 2.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:25.760,00:29:27.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And why should we do that?
Dialogue: 0,00:29:29.760,00:29:33.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Does that help us generate a system of equations for
Dialogue: 0,00:29:34.760,00:29:36.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,these points and weights?
Dialogue: 0,00:29:39.760,00:29:43.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Suppose a1 through al were equal to 0.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:44.760,00:29:47.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Does this formula have to work for that polynomial?
Dialogue: 0,00:29:47.760,00:29:52.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's now a0 times x to the 0th power of 1.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:52.760,00:29:54.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Does this polynomial have to be exact for that?
Dialogue: 0,00:29:54.760,00:29:57.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Yeah, alright. One condition.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:57.760,00:30:00.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,I throw away that term, and I throw away all the ones
Dialogue: 0,00:30:00.760,00:30:05.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,a2 through a, and a0, and I'm just left with a1x dx.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:05.760,00:30:07.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So that's my polynomial.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:07.760,00:30:11.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,I set a0 to 0, and a2 through al to 0.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:11.760,00:30:13.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Does this formula have to be exact for that one?
Dialogue: 0,00:30:14.760,00:30:15.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Yeah, sure.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:15.760,00:30:17.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because it has to be, this formula has to be exact
Dialogue: 0,00:30:17.760,00:30:19.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,for any L-thorough polynomial.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:19.760,00:30:24.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So each of those terms gives us one constraint.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:24.760,00:30:28.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,a0, the 0th-order polynomial, the 1st-order polynomial,
Dialogue: 0,00:30:28.760,00:30:30.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,the 2nd-order polynomial.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:30.760,00:30:32.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Each of those gives us a constraint
Dialogue: 0,00:30:32.760,00:30:35.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,that we can use to figure out the points and weights.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:35.760,00:30:39.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,In fact, it gives us exactly the number of constraints we need.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:39.760,00:30:42.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because we're going to set L equal to 2n minus 1.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:42.760,00:30:43.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So that's a1.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:43.760,00:30:49.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So that means we have 2n minus 1 degrees of freedom.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:49.760,00:30:53.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Or 2n, excuse me, 2n constraints for 2n degrees of freedom.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:53.760,00:31:00.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And then, what we want to be true is that
Dialogue: 0,00:31:00.760,00:31:03.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,given this exactness constraint,
Dialogue: 0,00:31:03.760,00:31:06.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,we can say then, if we take the monominal,
Dialogue: 0,00:31:06.760,00:31:08.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,the x to the L plus 1 monominal,
Dialogue: 0,00:31:08.760,00:31:10.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and take the difference between that,
Dialogue: 0,00:31:10.760,00:31:11.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,and integrating the,
Dialogue: 0,00:31:11.760,00:31:16.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,with this weights and points,
Dialogue: 0,00:31:16.760,00:31:20.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,that that error is going to be something like
Dialogue: 0,00:31:20.760,00:31:24.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,the remainder term in the Taylor series expansion.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:24.760,00:31:26.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And so I'm not going to do that too formally here.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:26.760,00:31:29.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's easy to find in basic textbooks.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:29.760,00:31:31.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,But that's the intuition to have in mind.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:31.760,00:31:36.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,When we do this, if we match for all the way up to L-thorough polynomials,
Dialogue: 0,00:31:36.760,00:31:40.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,what's left over, that remainder term has to be really small.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:41.760,00:31:47.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Right, so, can we do this?
Dialogue: 0,00:31:47.760,00:31:51.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,We have 2n degrees of freedom.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:51.760,00:31:53.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,We have 2n constraints.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:53.760,00:31:56.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,We could just set up the nonlinear system.
