Dialogue: 0,00:31:58.760,00:32:01.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So there's our set of constraints.
Dialogue: 0,00:32:01.760,00:32:05.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And we just have to make sure that the integral of the constant,
Dialogue: 0,00:32:05.760,00:32:07.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,the linear term, all the monomials,
Dialogue: 0,00:32:07.760,00:32:10.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,that that sum formula works for every single one of those cases.
Dialogue: 0,00:32:11.760,00:32:19.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,We have 2n equations in 2n degrees of freedom.
Dialogue: 0,00:32:19.760,00:32:21.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Is that a linear system of equations?
Dialogue: 0,00:32:21.760,00:32:26.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Can we solve that?
Dialogue: 0,00:32:26.760,00:32:27.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,00:32:27.760,00:32:33.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,I mean, what are our unknowns here?
Dialogue: 0,00:32:33.760,00:32:35.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,The ui and x?
Dialogue: 0,00:32:35.760,00:32:37.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you've got the points.
Dialogue: 0,00:32:37.760,00:32:39.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,What point, where are the points?
Dialogue: 0,00:32:39.760,00:32:41.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,And what are the weights?
Dialogue: 0,00:32:41.760,00:32:44.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So it's not a linear system of equations,
Dialogue: 0,00:32:44.760,00:32:48.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,because the terms and the equations are products of your unknowns.
Dialogue: 0,00:32:48.760,00:32:50.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is the nonlinear system of equations.
Dialogue: 0,00:32:50.760,00:32:55.760,辉英,,0,0,0,,So what method do you use to solve a nonlinear system of equations?
